# ============================================================================
# LOG MANAGEMENT NOTES
# ============================================================================

# LOG FILES:
# - Log files can grow large and contain sensitive information
# - Application logs often contain debugging information and error details
# - Web server logs may contain user IP addresses and request details

# SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS:
# - Log files may contain sensitive data (passwords, API keys in error messages)
# - Access logs can reveal user behavior and system usage patterns
# - Error logs may expose system vulnerabilities and configuration details

# STORAGE MANAGEMENT:
# - Log files can consume significant disk space over time
# - Consider implementing log rotation and retention policies
# - Use centralized logging solutions for production environments

# DEVELOPMENT PRACTICES:
# - Log files are regenerated during application execution
# - Different environments may produce different log contents
# - Test logs often contain temporary data and debugging information

# ============================================================================
# END OF LOGS PATTERNS
# ============================================================================

